"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Fix: Forward AWS SIGV4 env vars through tmux for Kiro E2E tests\n\n## Context\n\nAll Kiro E2E tests in CI fail with a login prompt timeout:\n```\nwaiting for kiro startup: timed out waiting for \"!>\" after 30s\n--- pane content ---\nYou are not logged in. Login now?\n```\n\n**Root cause:** Kiro authenticates via AWS SIGV4 env vars (`AMAZON_Q_SIGV4`, `AWS_REGION`, `AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID`, `AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY`, `AWS_SESSION_TOKEN`). These are set in the Go test process but **don't propagate through tmux** — tmux sessions inherit the server's environment, not the client's. All other agents (Claude, Droid, Gemini) store credentials in files, so they aren't affected.\n\n**Existing pattern:** Claude Code's `StartSession` already solves this by wrapping the command with `env KEY=VALUE ...` (see `e2e/agents/claude.go:192-194`). Kiro needs to follow the same pattern.\n\n## Changes\n\n### File: `e2e/agents/kiro.go` (only file modified)\n\n1. **Add `kiroAuthEnvArgs()` helper** — collects non-empty AWS auth env vars as `KEY=VALUE` strings\n   ```go\n   func kiroAuthEnvArgs() []string {\n       var args []string\n       for _, key := range []string{\"AMAZON_Q_SIGV4\", \"AWS_REGION\", \"AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID\", \"AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY\", \"AWS_SESSION_TOKEN\"} {\n           if v := os.Getenv(key); v != \"\" {\n               args = append(args, key+\"=\"+v)\n           }\n       }\n       return args\n   }\n   ```\n\n2. **Update `RunPrompt()`** (line 141) — wrap kiro-cli command with `env`:\n   ```go\n   // Before:\n   s, err := NewTmuxSession(name, dir, []string{\"ENTIRE_TEST_TTY\"}, k.Binary(), args...)\n\n   // After:\n   cmdArgs := append([]string{\"env\"}, kiroAuthEnvArgs()...)\n   cmdArgs = append(cmdArgs, k.Binary())\n   cmdArgs = append(cmdArgs, args...)\n   s, err := NewTmuxSession(name, dir, []string{\"ENTIRE_TEST_TTY\"}, cmdArgs[0], cmdArgs[1:]...)\n   ```\n\n3. **Update `StartSession()`** (line 180) — same pattern:\n   ```go\n   // Before:\n   s, err := NewTmuxSession(name, dir, []string{\"ENTIRE_TEST_TTY\"}, k.Binary(), \"chat\", \"-a\", \"--agent\", \"entire\")\n\n   // After:\n   cmdArgs := append([]string{\"env\"}, kiroAuthEnvArgs()...)\n   cmdArgs = append(cmdArgs, k.Binary(), \"chat\", \"-a\", \"--agent\", \"entire\")\n   s, err := NewTmuxSession(name, dir, []string{\"ENTIRE_TEST_TTY\"}, cmdArgs[0], cmdArgs[1:]...)\n   ```\n\n### No other files changed\n\n- `tmux.go` — no changes needed; `shellQuote` already handles all args\n- `Bootstrap()` — already reads env vars directly, works fine\n- Tests — existing E2E tests will validate the fix; `kiroAuthEnvArgs()` is trivial (loop over `os.Getenv`)\n\n## Why this is safe locally\n\nOn a dev machine where AWS vars aren't set, `kiroAuthEnvArgs()` returns nil. The command becomes `env kiro-cli chat ...`, which is equivalent to `kiro-cli chat ...` (POSIX standard behavior).\n\n## Verification\n\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint` — ensure code passes formatting and linting\n2. `mise run test:ci` — run unit + integration tests\n3. CI E2E tests with `--agent kiro` should now pass (Kiro receives the SIGV4 credentials)\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/alisha/.claude/projects/-Users-alisha-Projects-wt-kiro-oneshot/830ca3a0-928a-48b3-b00a-63e0c8a420fd.jsonl\n\n---\n\ncommit and push\n\n---\n\nsame issue\n\nRun mkdir -p \"$E2E_ARTIFACT_DIR\"\nartifacts: /home/runner/work/cli/cli/e2e-artifacts\n[e2e/tests]✖✖\n=== Failed\n=== FAIL: e2e/tests TestAttributionOnAgentCommit/kiro (15.19s)\n    attribution_test.go:54: start session: waiting for kiro startup prompt: timed out waiting for \"!>\" after 15s\n        --- pane content ---\n          You are not logged in. Login now?\n        ❯ Yes\n          No\n        --- end pane content ---\n\n=== FAIL: e2e/tests TestAttributionOnAgentCommit (15.19s)\n\nDONE 2 tests, 2 failures in 15